DESCRIPTION:Livestream link: https://vimeo.com/event/5770579\n\nThe Unitari
 an Universalist Church of Bloomington presents\nSavoy Soirée II\; or\, The 
 Very Model of a G&S Spectacular\nwith the Indiana University Gilbert and Su
 llivan Society\n\nJoin us for a lively evening of solos\, duets\, and ensem
 bles celebrating the wit\, sparkle\, and beauty of the operas of W. S. Gilb
 ert and Arthur Sullivan.\n\nNo tickets required—free and open to the public
 \; donations welcome\; a portion of the proceeds will support the Beacon “L
 ight the Way” campaign.\n\nEvent details:\nhttps://events.iu.edu/musiciub/e
 vent/2213241-university-gilbert-and-sullivan-society-savoy\n\n\nTrial by Ju
 ry (1875)\n\nNo. 3\, “All hail great Judge” \nMichael McGregor (Usher)\nCho
 rus of Bridesmaids and Jurymen\n\nNo. 4\, “When I\, good friends\, was call
 ’d to the bar” \nGuy Loftman (Learned Judge)\nChorus of Bridesmaids and Jur
 ymen\n\n\nThe Mikado\; or\, The Town of Titipu (1885)\n\nAct II\, No. 13\, 
 “The sun\, whose rays are all ablaze"\nLily Warren (Yum-Yum)\n\nAct I\, No.
  10\, “I am so proud” \nMichael McGregor (Pooh-Bah)\nSteve Krahnke (Ko-Ko)\
 nJohn M. Cowan (Pish-Tush)\n\n\nThe Yeomen of the Guard\; or\, The Merryman
  and His Maid (1888)\n\nAct II\, No. 15\, “Hereupon we’re both agreed” \nJo
 hn M. Cowan (Jack Point)\nPreston Rogers (Wilfred Shadbolt)\n\n\nThe Pirate
 s of Penzance\; or\, The Slave of Duty (1879)\n\nAct I\, No 13\, “I am the 
 very model of a modern Major-General” \nSteve Krahnke (Major-General Stanle
 y)\nChorus of Pirates and General Stanley’s Daughters\n\nAct II\, No. 24\, 
 “When a felon’s not engaged in his employment” \nMike McGregor (Sergeant of
  Police)\nChorus of Policemen\n\nAct I\, No. 14\, Finale\, “Hail Poetry”\nT
 utti Chorus\n\n\nPatience\; or\, Bunthorne’s Bride (1881)\n\nAct II\, No. 1
 3\, “A magnet hung in a hardware shop”\nJohn M. Cowan (Archibald Grosvenor)
 \nChorus of Maidens\n\n\nIolanthe\; or\, The Peer and the Peri (1882)\n\nAc
 t II\, No. 20 “Love\, unrequited … When you’re lying awake”\nSteven Warnock
  (Lord Chancellor)\n\nAct II\, No. 21 “If you go in” \nMike McGregor (Lord 
