  BCX0" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast="auto"><span class="No
 rmalTextRun SCXW4385479 BCX0">These amazing artists will discuss the crea
 tive and intercultural processes that shape their work\, including the in
 tegration of Hindustani musical traditions with contemporary Western comp
 ositional practices. Those attending will have the opportunity to ask que
 stions and gain insight into the artistic and cultural dimensions of cros
 s-genre music-making at the highest professional level.<br /><br /><stron
 g>Harmony and Power: A Summit on Cultural Diplomacy</strong><br /><br /><
 em>Presented by the Hamilton Lugar School and Jacobs School of Music<br /
 ></em><br />  With panel discussions\, presentations\, workshops\, and co
 ncerts\, Harmony and Power will explore how cultural diplomacy shapes pow
 er and global connections. Participants include renowned scholars\, pract
 itioners\, performers\, and students from a variety of disciplines.</span
 ></span><span class="LineBreakBlob BlobObject DragDrop SCXW4385479 BCX0">
 <br class="SCXW4385479 BCX0" /></span></span></p>
