SUMMARY:The Great Rewiring: Youth\, Social Media\, and the Future of Huma
 n Capital
DESCRIPTION:The Poynter Center presents "The Great Rewiring: Youth\, Soci
 al Media\, and the Future of Human Capital\," a conversation with 2025-26
  Poynter Chairs Jonathan Haidt and Jean Twenge.Haidt\, an author and soci
 al psychologist at New York University's Stern School of Business\, and T
 wenge\, a professor of psychology at San Diego State University who has w
 ritten more than 190 scientific publications and books\, will discuss the
  impact of social media and internet technology on young people and how i
 t bears on the future of our collective potential. Haidt will join the co
 nversation remotely\, while Twenge will participate in person at IU Cinem
 a. The conversation will be moderated by Todd Haugh\, professor of busine
 ss law and ethics at IU's Kelley School of Business and member of the boa
 rd of the Poynter Center.  This event is co-sponsored by the Institute of
  Corporate Governance + Ethics and Ethical Systems.Please contact Poynter
  Center Executive Director Indermohan Virk (ivirk@iu.edu) or Poynter Cent
 er Board Chair Elaine Monaghan (emonagha@iu.edu) for further details and 
 inquiries.  No tickets required
