X-SOURCE-URLS:{"IU Bloomington Libraries": "https://events.iu.edu/libraries/event/2219990-exhibit-from-the-pampas-to-indiana-discovering"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_libraries
X-SOURCE:IU Bloomington Libraries
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260312
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260313
LOCATION:William &amp\; Gayle Cook Music Library - Room Number: Lobby
GEO:39.164958;-86.517448
SUMMARY:Exhibit: From the Pampas to Indiana: Discovering Tango in Two Spe
 cial Collections
DESCRIPTION:Highlighting recent donations from Pablo Aslan (Fall 2024) an
 d Kristin Wendland (May 2025)\, this exhibit brings together complementar
 y perspectives that celebrate the passion\, history\, and enduring legacy
  of this beloved musical tradition.  On view from February 25 through Mar
 ch 15\, 2026\, the exhibit invites visitors to explore the sounds\, stori
 es\, and cultural richness of tango up close. This exhibit is part of the
  LAMC Tango Festival and is presented in celebration of the Latin America
 n Music Center's 65th Anniversary.  This exhibit is a collaboration of Em
 ma Dederick (LAMC Librarian and Curator of Special Collections) in partne
 rship with Music Librarianship students and LAMC Technical Services Assis
 tants\, Lauren O'Connor\, curator (MLS/MA Musicology student)\; Luz Ramir
 ez (undergraduate student in Violin Performance)\; and Lucy Rissmeyer (ML
 S/MA Musicology student).  Come experience the rhythm\, artistry\, and sp
 irit of tango.  The exhibit can be viewed during the Cook Music Library o
 pen hours. For the Library's hours\, visit: https://libraries.indiana.edu
 /cook-music-library (https://libraries.indiana.edu/cook-music-library)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Highlighting recent donations from Pabl
 o Aslan (Fall 2024) and Kristin Wendland (May 2025)\, this exhibit brings
  together complementary perspectives that celebrate the passion\, history
 \, and enduring legacy of this beloved musical tradition.</p><p>  On view
  from February 25 through March 15\, 2026\, the exhibit invites visitors 
 to explore the sounds\, stories\, and cultural richness of tango up close
 . This exhibit is part of the <strong>LAMC Tango Festival</strong> and is
  presented in celebration of the Latin American Music Center's 65th Anniv
 ersary.</p><p>  This exhibit is a collaboration of Emma Dederick (LAMC Li
 brarian and Curator of Special Collections) in partnership with Music Lib
 rarianship students and LAMC Technical Services Assistants\, Lauren O'Con
 nor\, curator (MLS/MA Musicology student)\; Luz Ramirez (undergraduate st
 udent in Violin Performance)\; and Lucy Rissmeyer (MLS/MA Musicology stud
 ent).</p><p>  Come experience the rhythm\, artistry\, and spirit of tango
 .</p><p>  The exhibit can be viewed during the Cook Music Library open ho
 urs. For the Library's hours\, visit: <a href="https://libraries.indiana.
 edu/cook-music-library">https://libraries.indiana.edu/cook-music-library<
 /a></p>
