X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Eskenazi Museum of Art": "https://events.iu.edu/artmuseum/event/2101091-homeschool-day-shapes-and-structures"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_eskenazi_museum
X-SOURCE:Eskenazi Museum of Art
DTSTART:20260312T140000Z
DTEND:20260312T160000Z
LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Homeschool Day: Shapes and Structures
DESCRIPTION:Students will look closely at the museum's special triangular
  shape and learn how new building materials changed the way architects de
 signed structures. Back in the studio\, we'll create our own floor plans 
 and models inspired by architect I.M. Pei's creative use of shapes and sp
 ace.Know Before You Go:  Meet us on the 1st floor of the museum at 10 a.m
 . Together\, we'll drop off personal items in the Simpson Center for Educ
 ation before exploring the galleries. After seeing artworks that will ins
 pire our project\, we'll head back to the Roehm Family Art-Making Studio 
 to create our own masterpieces! Don't forget to dress for a mess!  Stroll
 ers are welcome. Chaperones required. We ask that chaperones be 18 or old
 er\, with one adult for every 6 children.Parking Information:  The museum
  is in the pedestrian district of campus with several parking options nea
 rby. The Indiana Memorial Union lot (900 E. 7th Street) is just a 5-minut
 e walk diagonal to the museum\, and visitors can receive 40% off parking 
 validation at the museum's guest services desk. The East Garage (105 N. E
 agleson Ave.) and Fee Lane Garage (709 N. Fee Lane) are also convenient\,
  about an 8–10 minute walk. Learn more about parking on the Bloomington
  campus here (https://parking.indiana.edu/facilities/index.html).
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Students will look closely at the museu
 m's special triangular shape and learn how new building materials changed
  the way architects designed structures. Back in the studio\, we'll creat
 e our own floor plans and models inspired by architect I.M. Pei's creativ
 e use of shapes and space.</p><p><strong>Know Before You Go:</strong></p>
 <p>  Meet us on the 1st floor of the museum at 10 a.m. Together\, we'll d
 rop off personal items in the Simpson Center for Education before explori
 ng the galleries. After seeing artworks that will inspire our project\, w
 e'll head back to the Roehm Family Art-Making Studio to create our own ma
 sterpieces! Don't forget to dress for a mess!</p><p>  Strollers are welco
 me. Chaperones required. We ask that chaperones be 18 or older\, with one
  adult for every 6 children.</p><p><strong>Parking Information:</strong><
 /p><p>  The museum is in the pedestrian district of campus with several p
 arking options nearby. The Indiana Memorial Union lot (900 E. 7th Street)
  is just a 5-minute walk diagonal to the museum\, and visitors can receiv
 e 40% off parking validation at the museum's guest services desk. The Eas
 t Garage (105 N. Eagleson Ave.) and Fee Lane Garage (709 N. Fee Lane) are
  also convenient\, about an 8–10 minute walk. Learn more about parking 
 on the Bloomington campus <a href="https://parking.indiana.edu/facilities
 /index.html">here</a>.</p>
