X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Eskenazi Museum of Art": "https://events.iu.edu/artmuseum/event/2198077-homeschool-day-shapes-and-structures-pm-session"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_eskenazi_museum
X-SOURCE:Eskenazi Museum of Art
DTSTART:20260312T170000Z
DTEND:20260312T190000Z
LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART - Room Number: Simpson Ce
 nter for Education
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Homeschool Day: Shapes and Structures PM Session
DESCRIPTION:Students will look closely at the museum's special triangular
  shape and learn how new building materials changed the way architects de
 signed structures. Back in the studio\, we'll create our own floor plans 
 and models inspired by architect I.M. Pei's creative use of shapes and sp
 ace.Know Before You Go:  Meet us on the 1st floor of the museum at 1 p.m.
  Together\, we'll drop off personal items in the Simpson Center for Educa
 tion before exploring the galleries. After seeing artworks that will insp
 ire our project\, we'll head back to the Roehm Family Art-Making Studio t
 o create our own masterpieces! Don't forget to dress for a mess!  Strolle
 rs are welcome. Chaperones required. We ask that chaperones be 18 or olde
 r\, with one adult for every 6 children.Parking Information:  The museum 
 is in the pedestrian district of campus with several parking options near
 by. The Indiana Memorial Union lot (900 E. 7th Street) is just a 5-minute
  walk diagonal to the museum\, and visitors can receive 40% off parking v
 alidation at the museum's guest services desk. The East Garage (105 N. Ea
 gleson Ave.) and Fee Lane Garage (709 N. Fee Lane) are also convenient\, 
 about an 8–10 minute walk. Learn more about parking on the Bloomington 
 campus here (https://parking.indiana.edu/facilities/index.html).
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Students will look closely at the museu
 m's special triangular shape and learn how new building materials changed
  the way architects designed structures. Back in the studio\, we'll creat
 e our own floor plans and models inspired by architect I.M. Pei's creativ
 e use of shapes and space.</p><p><strong>Know Before You Go:</strong></p>
 <p>  Meet us on the 1st floor of the museum at 1 p.m. Together\, we'll dr
 op off personal items in the Simpson Center for Education before explorin
 g the galleries. After seeing artworks that will inspire our project\, we
 'll head back to the Roehm Family Art-Making Studio to create our own mas
 terpieces! Don't forget to dress for a mess!</p><p>  Strollers are welcom
 e. Chaperones required. We ask that chaperones be 18 or older\, with one 
 adult for every 6 children.</p><p><strong>Parking Information:</strong></
 p><p>  The museum is in the pedestrian district of campus with several pa
 rking options nearby. The Indiana Memorial Union lot (900 E. 7th Street) 
 is just a 5-minute walk diagonal to the museum\, and visitors can receive
  40% off parking validation at the museum's guest services desk. The East
  Garage (105 N. Eagleson Ave.) and Fee Lane Garage (709 N. Fee Lane) are 
 also convenient\, about an 8–10 minute walk. Learn more about parking o
 n the Bloomington campus <a href="https://parking.indiana.edu/facilities/
 index.html">here</a>.</p>
