CATEGORIES:ThoughtfulLearning
CATEGORIES:Engage & Thrive - Wellbeing
DESCRIPTION:Recovery Ally Training is an educational workshop designed to 
 increase awareness\, reduce stigma\, and build practical skills to suppor
 t individuals in recovery from substance use disorders. Participants will
  learn about recovery pathways\, common challenges faced by people in rec
 overy\, and how language\, policies\, and everyday interactions can eithe
 r support or hinder recovery efforts.\nThis training emphasizes empathy\,
  inclusivity\, and actionable strategies\, empowering participants to ser
 ve as visible\, informed allies within their communities\, workplaces\, o
 r campuses. By the end of the training\, attendees will have a stronger u
 nderstanding of recovery-oriented practices and how to create safer\, mor
 e supportive environments for people in recovery.\n\nHosted by: Collegiat
 e Recovery Community\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://b
 einvolved.indiana.edu/event/12164768
DTEND:20260312T223000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260312T210000Z
LOCATION:The Wellness House 115
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CANCELLED
SUMMARY:Recovery Ally Training
