GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Visiting Artist: Jade Guanaro Kuriki-Olivo (Puppies Puppies)
DESCRIPTION:Kuriki-Olivo is known for her conceptual works of sculpture\,
  installation\, and performance that combine readymade objects\, popular 
 culture\, and autobiography to address themes of transgender identity\, r
 ace\, and power in contemporary society. Her 2017 work Liberté (Liberty)
 \, was the first and only work of performance art to be acquired by the W
 hitney Museum of American Art for its permanent collection.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Kuriki-Olivo is known for her conceptua
 l works of sculpture\, installation\, and performance that combine readym
 ade objects\, popular culture\, and autobiography to address themes of tr
 ansgender identity\, race\, and power in contemporary society. Her 2017 w
 ork <i>Liberté (Liberty</i>)\, was the first and only work of performanc
 e art to be acquired by the Whitney Museum of American Art for its perman
 ent collection.</p>
