CATEGORIES:Leadership & Engagement
CATEGORIES:Emotional Wellness
DESCRIPTION:This MAP Session is the fourth out of six sessions in Spring 2
 026. In this session\, we'll learn about "compassion fatigue\," how it im
 pacts leaders\, and\, most importantly\, how to navigate and minimize it.
 \nThe Mentor Apprenticeship Program (MAP) is a two-semester training seri
 es facilitated by the FASE Mentoring Program. It gives students at IU Blo
 omington opportunities to enhance their mentoring\, teamwork\, and leader
 ship skills. Upon completion of MAP\, students receive a Certificate of C
 ompletion\, which establishes their commitment to growth and leadership.\
 nAll Indiana University events\, groups\, activities\, and educational\, 
 cultural\, and historical observances welcome all IU students and other m
 embers of the Indiana University community.\n\nHosted by: Mentoring Servi
 ces and Leadership Development \n\nAdditional Information can be found at
 : https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11350136
DTEND:20260312T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260312T220000Z
LOCATION:300 North Eagleson Ave
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:MAP Session 25-26: Battling Compassion Fatigue
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11350136
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11350136
X-HOSTS:Mentoring Services and Leadership Development
END:VEVENT
