BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"IU Auditorium": "https://events.iu.edu/iu-auditorium/event/2031511-silkroad-ensemble-with-rhiannon-giddens"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_auditorium
X-SOURCE:IU Auditorium
DTSTART:20260312T233000Z
DTEND:20260313T003000Z
LOCATION:AUDITORIUM
GEO:39.168443;-86.517858
SUMMARY:Silkroad Ensemble with Rhiannon Giddens
DESCRIPTION:The Silkroad Ensemble's latest flagship program with Artistic
  Director Rhiannon Giddens is Sanctuary: The Power of Resonance and Ritua
 l. In this program\, Giddens and the ensemble explore how to experience m
 usic to better understand the world\, find comfort\, process loss in a ch
 anging environment\, and rebuild community based on humanity. Historicall
 y\, when people have found themselves in a time of conflict or stress\, t
 hey have always turned to music.  &#160\;  The idea of trance\, something
  that can bring a deep peace that is hard to find in modern society\, is 
 profoundly tied to the communal music-making traditions found in many dif
 ferent cultures\, from Morocco to India to Ireland\, and is a way to buil
 d a stronger human connection amidst all the noise. In Sanctuary: The Pow
 er of Resonance and Ritual\, the musicians will delve deeply into one ano
 ther's music and traditions\, such as Sicilian tarantella with Mauro Dura
 nte and Francesco Turrisi\, Moroccan gnawa with Mehdi Nassouli\, Indian c
 lassical music with Sandeep Das\, American old-time with Giddens on banjo
 \, and more\, and invite audiences to join them as partners and participa
 nts in the performance\, instead of solely as passive bystanders.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The Silkroad Ensemble's latest flagship
  program with Artistic Director Rhiannon Giddens is <i>Sanctuary: The Pow
 er of Resonance and Ritual</i>. In this program\, Giddens and the ensembl
 e explore how to experience music to better understand the world\, find c
 omfort\, process loss in a changing environment\, and rebuild community b
 ased on humanity. Historically\, when people have found themselves in a t
 ime of conflict or stress\, they have always turned to music.</p><p>  &#1
 60\;</p><p>  The idea of trance\, something that can bring a deep peace t
 hat is hard to find in modern society\, is profoundly tied to the communa
 l music-making traditions found in many different cultures\, from Morocco
  to India to Ireland\, and is a way to build a stronger human connection 
 amidst all the noise. In <i>Sanctuary: The Power of Resonance and Ritual<
 /i>\, the musicians will delve deeply into one another's music and tradit
 ions\, such as Sicilian tarantella with Mauro Durante and Francesco Turri
 si\, Moroccan gnawa with Mehdi Nassouli\, Indian classical music with San
 deep Das\, American old-time with Giddens on banjo\, and more\, and invit
 e audiences to join them as partners and participants in the performance\
 , instead of solely as passive bystanders.</p>
