SUMMARY:Intermediate Crochet With Lindsey Alumbaugh
DESCRIPTION:This workshop will walk you through how to make a Pacific Halibut Plush\, with pattern provided by the National Park Services! You will learn intermediate techniques such as treble crochet\, quadruple crochet\, DC2TOG\, and more!  \nSaturdays\, March 14 & 21\, 2026\, 1:00 – 4:00 PM \n$45 BSWG members \n$55 non-BSWG student members (includes one-year guild student membership) \n$75 non-BSWG members (includes one-year guild membership) \nClass size 2-10 students \nStudents must know basic crocheting.  \nThe instructor will provide all supplies or you may bring your own. Art Remains is a great option for sourcing supplies if you wish to bring your own.  \nRegister Here \n\n           Download QR
