GEO:39.165074;-86.526424
SUMMARY:Breaking Tradition: America's 250th Birthday!
DESCRIPTION:Professor Randy Kozel of the University of Notre Dame Law Sch
 ool\, joined by Professor William Popkin\, will explore how we\, as law s
 tudents\, lawyers\, and judges\, interpret our Constitution in light of i
 ts history and tradition. What relationship does the history and traditio
 ns approach to constitutional interpretation have to other interpretive m
 ethods? How does this system of interpretation influence the shaping of A
 merican law today? Join us to celebrate America's 250th birthday!  BuffaL
 ouie's will be provided for all attendees
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Professor Randy Kozel of the University
  of Notre Dame Law School\, joined by Professor William Popkin\, will exp
 lore how we\, as law students\, lawyers\, and judges\, interpret our Cons
 titution in light of its history and tradition. What relationship does th
 e history and traditions approach to constitutional interpretation have t
 o other interpretive methods? How does this system of interpretation infl
 uence the shaping of American law today? Join us to celebrate America's 2
 50th birthday!</p><p>  BuffaLouie's will be provided for all attendees</p
 >
