LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART - Room Number: Roehm Fami
 ly Art-making Studio
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Open Studio
DESCRIPTION:Our Open Studio program invites participants to create in the
  museum's art studio\, where art becomes a tool for reflection\, expressi
 on\, and connection. Guided by a trained art therapist\, the open studio 
 welcomes visitors to engage with materials at their own pace while drawin
 g inspiration from the surrounding exhibitions. No art experience is need
 ed\; just bring your curiosity and a desire to create\, and we'll handle 
 the rest!  Participants are welcome to utilize supplies located in the st
 udio\, as well as bring their own supplies/projects to work on.  This gro
 up meets on the 2nd and 4th Wednesday of every month\, excluding holidays
  and museum closures. It is open to everyone: students\, staff\, and the 
 public included! The group will meet in the Roehm Family Art-making Studi
 o\, located inside the Simpson Center for Education on the 2nd floor of t
 he Eskenazi Museum of Art.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Our Open Studio program invites partici
 pants to create in the museum's art studio\, where art becomes a tool for
  reflection\, expression\, and connection. Guided by a trained art therap
 ist\, the open studio welcomes visitors to engage with materials at their
  own pace while drawing inspiration from the surrounding exhibitions. No 
 art experience is needed\; just bring your curiosity and a desire to crea
 te\, and we'll handle the rest!</p><p>  Participants are welcome to utili
 ze supplies located in the studio\, as well as bring their own supplies/p
 rojects to work on.</p><p>  This group meets on the 2nd and 4th Wednesday
  of every month\, excluding holidays and museum closures. It is open to e
 veryone: students\, staff\, and the public included! The group will meet 
 in the Roehm Family Art-making Studio\, located inside the Simpson Center
  for Education on the 2nd floor of the Eskenazi Museum of Art.</p>
