SUMMARY: AlgoRhythms: AI\, Music\, and Human-Centered Creativity
DESCRIPTION:Indiana University Jacobs School of Music\, partnered with th
 e Maurer School of Law\, IU Innovates\, Music Tectonics\, and the AI+Digi
 tal Futures Team\, presents AlgoRhythms 2026\, March 26–28 in Bloomington
  and online. This multi-day conference brings together artists\, scholars
 \, technologists\, educators\, and industry professionals to explore how 
 artificial intelligence is transforming music creation\, ownership\, and 
 the future of creative work.\n\nThursday\, March 26\n12:00 PM — Legal Tre
 nds in Music & AI\nA discussion examining current legal developments shap
 ing AI’s role in music.\nMoot Courtroom\, Maurer School of Law | Streamin
 g online\n\n1:30 PM — Legal Challenges and Opportunities in Music & AI\nA
  panel exploring emerging legal questions around authorship\, rights\, an
 d industry impact.\nMoot Courtroom\, Maurer School of Law | Streaming onl
 ine\n\n4:00 PM — Who Owns the Muse? Authenticity\, Agency & AI in Music C
 reation\nA conversation on creativity\, authorship\, and artistic identit
 y in the age of AI.\nLocation TBA | Streaming online\n\nSign up here http
 s://forms.office.com/pages/responsepage.aspx?id=NL4TEdGuAE2rS83QJRC-kdRT0
 NpCm_pFldrMPyyiXzVUMFRGSUg0V0lHV1BTTkJBSTVLOUFLUlRVMS4u&route=shorturl to
  attend either the in-person or virtual panel discussions.
CATEGORIES:
