SUMMARY:Global Competencies Skills Development Series: From Indiana to Am
 bassador—Lessons from a Global Career
DESCRIPTION:Lead with relevance to the audience. Make the Foreign Service
  connection explicit.  Here's a tighter\, more targeted version:Join Amba
 ssador Maria Brewer for an off-the-record dinner with Hamilton Lugar Scho
 ol students. Dinner will be provided.  A two-time U.S. Ambassador and Ind
 iana native\, Ambassador Brewer built her career in the U.S. Foreign Serv
 ice\, leading missions in Africa and South Asia and managing complex dipl
 omatic negotiations.  If you are exploring a career in the Foreign Servic
 e or international policy\, this is a rare opportunity for candid access.
  Hear how assignments are chosen\, how reputations are built\, and how le
 aders navigate pressure overseas.  Come with real questions. Leave with c
 larity about what this path demands and what it offers.
