DESCRIPTION:This MAP Session is the fifth out of six sessions for the Spri
 ng 2026 Semester. In this session\, we will talk about how to identify\, 
 and prevent\, burnout as a student leader. \nThe Mentor Apprenticeship Pr
 ogram (MAP) is a two-semester training series facilitated by the FASE Men
 toring Program. It gives students at IU Bloomington opportunities to enha
 nce their mentoring\, teamwork\, and leadership skills. Upon completion o
 f MAP\, students receive a Certificate of Completion\, which establishes 
 their commitment to growth and leadership.\nAll Indiana University events
 \, groups\, activities\, and educational\, cultural\, and historical obse
 rvances welcome all IU students and other members of the Indiana Universi
 ty community.\n\nHosted by: Mentoring Services and Leadership Development
  \n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.e
 du/event/11350132
