BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"IU beINvolved Student Orgs": "https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11321015"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_campuslabs
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
CATEGORIES:ThoughtfulLearning
CATEGORIES:Leadership
CATEGORIES:Leadership & Engagement
CATEGORIES:Intellectual Wellness
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the Student Involvement and Leadership Center’s Br
 idgework Series\, a monthly leadership and organizational development ser
 ies designed to help students strengthen their team-building skills\, und
 erstand group dynamics\, and become agents of change within their organiz
 ations and communities. Each session will center around a key aspect of h
 ow groups work—from communication and collaboration to culture-building a
 nd creating sustainable impact—through interactive activities and real-wo
 rld leadership scenarios.\nThis 8-event series (spanning the academic yea
 r) provides an engaging space for students to connect across campus\, lea
 rn the foundations of effective teamwork\, and explore how they can contr
 ibute to meaningful change.\nWhether you're leading a student org\, suppo
 rting a team\, or just getting started\, Bridgework offers practical tool
 s and powerful insights to help you build better bridges—between people\,
  ideas\, and action.\n \n<!--StartFragment -->\n📅 March 26th\, 2026⏰ 6:0
 0 PM – 8:00 PM📍 IMU Frangipani Room\n💡 Strong teams don’t happen by cha
 nce—they’re built with intention. In "Culture of Connection\," the penult
 imate event in the Bridgework Series\, we’ll continue our exploration of 
 the Group Dynamics domain of the Student Leadership Competencies\, equipp
 ing you with the strategies 🔗 to foster trust\, create inclusive environ
 ments\, and strengthen the relational fabric of your organization.\n🔥 A 
 thriving team culture is the foundation of success. Let’s dive into how t
 o cultivate connection and collaboration that lasts!\nAll Indiana Univers
 ity events\, groups\, activities\, and educational\, cultural\, and histo
 rical observances welcome all IU students and other members of the Indian
 a University community.\n<!--EndFragment -->\n\nHosted by: Student Involv
 ement and Leadership Center\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: ht
 tps://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11321015
DTEND:20260327T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260326T220000Z
LOCATION:IMU Frangipani Room
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:SILC BridgeWork Series - "Culture of Connection"
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11321015
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11321015
