  Music Tech PlaygroundIU Innovates | In Person Only    Sponsored by Sweet
 water SoundFeaturing Moises\, SongHub\, Zinstrel\, EDGE Sound Research\, 
 Soloist\, PetsAloud\, and others    Live demonstrations and discussions t
 hroughout the day.    .  6:00–8:00 p.m. — ReceptionGraduate Hotel | I
 n Person Only    Sponsored by the IU Office of the Chancellor  The summit
  provides an opportunity to wrestle with questions about authorship\, own
 ership\, environmental impact\, cultural disruption\, business transforma
 tion\, and the meaning of creativity itself.  Primary partners for this p
 roject are the Maurer School of Law\, IU Innovates\, Music Tectonics\, an
 d the AI+Digital Futures Team.  AlgoRhythms is generously supported by Fr
 ank Graves\, whose contributions to the Jacobs School of Music and Indian
 a University are deeply appreciated. Additional funding is made possible 
 through the generous support of the Office of the Vice President for Rese
 arch in Arts &amp\; Humanities\, IU Innovates\, the Bloomington Office of
  the Chancellor\, the Maurer School of Law\, and Sweetwater Sound.
