SUMMARY:Global Competencies Skills Development Series: Power Moves – Le
 vel Up Your Networking Without Freaking Out in International Circles
DESCRIPTION:Intimidated by networking in international settings? Step int
 o a live embassy reception simulation with Ambassador Maria Brewer and pr
 actice the skills global professionals rely on. Snacks will be provided. 
  In this interactive session\, you will:      Make formal introductions i
 n a diplomatic setting          Navigate hierarchy and cultural protocol 
          Practice engaging senior leaders with confidence      You will r
 eceive direct feedback from a former two-time U.S. Ambassador who led mis
 sions in Africa and served in senior roles across the State Department.  
 Walk away with a clear\, repeatable approach to high-level networking you
  can use at career fairs\, conferences\, and internships this semester.  
 This is hands-on. Not a lecture.  If you are considering the Foreign Serv
 ice\, international policy\, or any global career\, this is practical tra
 ining you can apply immediately.  Space is limited to ensure meaningful f
 eedback.  Part of the Hamilton Lugar Global Competencies Skills Developme
 nt Series.
