DESCRIPTION:<br><br><h2><b>Bloomington Trivia Championship Series</b></h2><
 h3><b>Held at the Pavilion in <a href="https://switchyardpark.com/"><u>Swit
 chyard Park</u></a></b></h3><h4><b>2026 Trivia Nights<br>7-9 p.m.\; doors o
 pen at 6 p.m.</b></h4><ul><li>Friday\, Jan. 16</li><li>Friday\, March 27</l
 i><li>Friday\, May 29</li><li>Friday\, July 17</li><li>Friday\, Sept. 11</l
 i><li>Friday\, Nov. 6</li></ul><p><a href="https://webtrac.bloomington.in.g
 ov/webtrac/web/search.html?Primarycode=165001"><u>Registration fee is $160 
 per team for the entire series. Register for all six trivia nights by Jan. 
 16 and save $32!</u></a></p><p><a href="https://webtrac.bloomington.in.gov/
 webtrac/web/search.html?Primarycode=165001"><u>Registration deadline is the
  day of the event.</u></a></p><h4><b>Who will be crowned Bloomington’s Triv
 ia Champion?</b></h4><p>The winning team from each night will automatically
  qualify for the Championship Night. Cumulative point leaders also have a c
 hance to qualify. At the end of the series\, the top teams will compete to 
