SUMMARY:Lotus Presents: Making Movies
DESCRIPTION:Friday March 27th at 8:00 pm\n*doors open at 7:00 pm \nWhere: The BlockHouse Bar 21+\, 205 S College Ave\nSliding fee $10 – $25\, Pay at the door \n \nAbout Making Movies\nMaking Movies (3/25/26 – 3/27/26) A dynamic band that blends Afro-Latino rhythms and rock ’n’ roll with African-derived percussion and styles like rumba\, merengue\, mambo\, and cumbia. Founded by Enrique Chi—a Panamanian songwriter\, musician\, filmmaker\, and cultural producer—the Latin Grammy-nominated band serves as the primary platform for Chi’s creative mission. Armed with electric guitars and a mejoranera\, a folkloric guitar native to Panamá\, the band interweaves styles as divergent as cumbia and blues\, salsa\, soul\, and rock’n’roll––all boiled down into their own original sound.
URL:https://www.lotusfest.org/event/lotus-presents-making-movies/
LOCATION:Blockhouse Bar\, 205 S. College Avenue\, Bloomington\, Indiana\, 47404\, United States
CATEGORIES:Lotus Blossoms,Lotus Blossoms Public Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://www.lotusfest.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/20240404_MakingMovies_BlockHouse_ShakilaShrestha-_-130.webp
END:VEVENT
