 />    - Tristra Newyear Yeager (Music Tectonics)<br />    - Timirah James
  (Artist\, AI Music researcher)<br />    -&#160\; Andy West (IU Jacobs Sc
 hool of Music)  </li></ul><p>  The summit provides an opportunity to wres
 tle with questions about authorship\, ownership\, environmental impact\, 
 cultural disruption\, business transformation\, and the meaning of creati
 vity itself.</p><p>  Primary partners for this project are the Maurer Sch
 ool of Law\, IU Innovates\, Music Tectonics\, and the AI+Digital Futures 
 Team.</p><p>  AlgoRhythms is generously supported by Frank Graves\, whose
  contributions to the Jacobs School of Music and Indiana University are d
 eeply appreciated. Additional funding is made possible through the genero
 us support of the Office of the Vice President for Research in Arts &amp\
 ; Humanities\, IU Innovates\, the Bloomington Office of the Chancellor\, 
 the Maurer School of Law\, and Sweetwater Sound.</p><p><picture class="lw
