CATEGORIES:ThoughtfulLearning
DESCRIPTION:The Pre-PA club is conducting a phlebotomy course\, led by Nic
 holas Perrotta\, where he will teach pre-PA and other IU students valuabl
 e venipuncture skills. Upon completion of the course\, the students will 
 receive a phlebotomy certification lasting up to two years.\nThe training
  length is 2 days\, Saturday\, March 28th and Sunday\, March 29th. On Sun
 day\, clinic usually wraps up around 2:30pm\, with an optional discussion
  afterward about strategies\, fielding questions about job/volunteer oppo
 rtunities as a phlebotomist\, etc. This is a challenging and rewarding cl
 inic that will be of great value students as they continue their health c
 areer. \n"Nick is a very experienced instructor (20+ years) who has not o
 nly been teaching university students but also several hospitals’ researc
 h staff and county public health departments and he has a diverse researc
 h background."\nNote: Certification is valid anywhere in the United State
 s for two years from certification date with the exception of: California
 \, Washington State\, Nevada\, Louisiana (there are a different in-state 
 training/licensing\, so if you need it there\, contact appropriate agency
  and find out about requirements and exemptions)\; students have also dra
 wn blood in other countries. There are a number of places around the coun
 try including the Midwest\, and your Bloomington campus where students ha
 ve gained employment after clinic.\n\nHosted by: Pre-Physician Assistant 
 Club at IU\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://beinvolved.
 indiana.edu/event/11912208
DTEND:20260329T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260328T110000Z
LOCATION:Global & International Studies\, GA 1100
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Pre-PA Club Phlebotomy Class
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11912208
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11912208
