DESCRIPTION:Have you ever seen a crazy quilt? Stop by the Wylie House in Ma
 rch to see Rebecca Wylie's 100+ year-old crazy quilt\, a beautiful patchwor
 k of fabric filled with embroidery. Then come to the education center and l
 earn how to stitch those same designs onto your own felt ornament.\n\nFree 
 event for families\, students\, and friends of all ages.\n\nNote: Museum wa
 s closed March 14 & 21 for Spring Break.\n\nContact: Kaia Wells\, kaiwells@
 iu.edu\, (812) 855-6224
LAST-MODIFIED:20260218T191542Z
LOCATION:Wylie House Museum\, 307 E 2nd St\, Bloomington\, IN 47401\, USA
