GEO:39.165074;-86.526424
SUMMARY:Litigating Faculty First Amendment Rights
DESCRIPTION:The "Litigating Faculty First Amendment Rights" program will 
 explore current litigation surrounding the question of faculty First Amen
 dment rights related to teaching and academic speech. Kilborn\, plaintiff
 /appellant in a recent case at the Seventh Circuit\, will describe how he
  came to challenge threats of discipline from his university in a case th
 at broke important new ground in this federal judicial circuit for the Fi
 rst Amendment rights of public university faculty. Bleisch\, an expert on
  the First Amendment and universities\, will provide broader doctrinal co
 ntext and discuss similar recent cases around the country. Sanders will d
 irect questions to the two speakers and will moderate.Jason Kilborn\, Pro
 fessor of Law\, University of Illinois Chicago School of Law  Josh Bleisc
 h\, Staff Attorney\, ACLU of Indiana  Steve Sanders\, IU Maurer School of
  Law
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The "Litigating Faculty First Amendment
  Rights" program will explore current litigation surrounding the question
  of faculty First Amendment rights related to teaching and academic speec
 h. Kilborn\, plaintiff/appellant in a recent case at the Seventh Circuit\
 , will describe how he came to challenge threats of discipline from his u
 niversity in a case that broke important new ground in this federal judic
 ial circuit for the First Amendment rights of public university faculty. 
 Bleisch\, an expert on the First Amendment and universities\, will provid
 e broader doctrinal context and discuss similar recent cases around the c
 ountry. Sanders will direct questions to the two speakers and will modera
 te.</p><ul><li>Jason Kilborn\, Professor of Law\, University of Illinois 
 Chicago School of Law  </li><li>Josh Bleisch\, Staff Attorney\, ACLU of I
 ndiana  </li><li>Steve Sanders\, IU Maurer School of Law  </li></ul>
UID:20260330T160000Z-2224077@events.iu.edu
DTSTAMP:20260227T164414Z
URL:https://events.iu.edu/lawiub/event/2224077-litigating-faculty-first-a
 mendment-rights
LAST-MODIFIED:20260227T214414Z
