SUMMARY:Toddler Time: Underwater Explorers
DESCRIPTION:Swim through the gallery as we explore works of art inspired 
 by life under the sea. Together\, we'll practice careful gallery walking 
 and make close observations. Then\, dive into hands-on artmaking by creat
 ing your own coral reef\, encouraging creativity while developing fine mo
 tor skills.Adult chaperone required. Children must be accompanied by a ca
 regiver at all times.Strollers &amp\; bags. We love strollers! When carry
 ing small children\, please keep them in front of you. Large bags can be 
 stored in our lockers or in the art studio prior to our gallery walk.Lear
 n more about parking\, accessibility\, and museum guidelineshere (https:/
 /artmuseum.indiana.edu/visit/your-visit.html).
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Swim through the gallery as we explore 
 works of art inspired by life under the sea. Together\, we'll practice ca
 reful gallery walking and make close observations. Then\, dive into hands
 -on artmaking by creating your own coral reef\, encouraging creativity wh
 ile developing fine motor skills.</p><p><strong data-start="70" data-end=
 "99">Adult chaperone required.</strong> Children must be accompanied by a
  caregiver at all times.<br /><strong data-start="566" data-end="587">Str
 ollers &amp\; bags.</strong> We love strollers! When carrying small child
 ren\, please keep them in front of you. Large bags can be stored in our l
 ockers or in the art studio prior to our gallery walk.</p><p><span class=
 "TextRun SCXW184603341 BCX0" lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" data-contrast=
 "none"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW184603341 BCX0">Learn more about pa
 rking\, accessibility\, and museum guidelines</span></span><a href="https
 ://artmuseum.indiana.edu/visit/your-visit.html">here</a>.</p>
