DESCRIPTION:This film event is part of&#160\;First&#160\;Thursdays.&#160\
 ;&#160\;About the film: When the massive Thirty Meter Telescope is propos
 ed to be built on Mauna Kea\, an uprising of&#160\;kiaʻi&#160\;(protecto
 rs) in Hawaiʻi and around the world dedicate their lives to protecting t
 he sacred mountain from destruction. Through the lens of mothers and daug
 hters in three Native Hawaiian families\,&#160\;Standing Above the Clouds
 &#160\;explores intergenerational healing and the impacts of safeguarding
  cultural traditions.&#160\;&#160\;All Indiana University events\, groups
 \, activities\, and&#160\;educational\, cultural\, and historical observa
 nces welcome all IU students and other members of the Indiana University 
 community.For more information\, view this event in BeInvolved (https://b
 einvolved.indiana.edu/event/12298599).
