SUMMARY:Global Competencies Skills Development Series: How to Work a Room
  and Land Your Dream Job
DESCRIPTION:Curious how to turn conferences\, networking\, and small conv
 ersations into real career opportunities? Join Erin Huntington\, retired 
 VP of International Corporate Affairs at Eli Lilly\, for a hands-on sessi
 on designed to give you the insider playbook for global careers.  Erin bu
 ilt a career bridging government service and international corporate stra
 tegy\, managing global teams and connecting policy\, advocacy\, and marke
 t access for one of the world's leading pharmaceutical companies. She'll 
 share real-world strategies that helped her move from Capitol Hill to glo
 bal leadership—and how you can apply them too.What you'll get out of th
 is session:      How to approach professionals\, start conversations\, an
 d make connections that matter          Insider strategies for turning ne
 tworking into internships\, mentors\, and career opportunities          T
 ools to tell your story confidently in interviews and professional settin
 gs          Tips for navigating global conferences and international prof
 essional spaces      This drop-in session is open to all HLS students. Li
 ght refreshments will be provided. Don't miss the chance to get concrete 
 strategies that you can use immediately at conferences\, internships\, an
 d global career events.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p data-start="227" data-end="496">  Curious
  how to turn conferences\, networking\, and small conversations into real
  career opportunities? Join Erin Huntington\, retired VP of International
  Corporate Affairs at Eli Lilly\, for a hands-on session designed to give
  you the insider playbook for global careers.</p><p data-start="498" data
 -end="842">  Erin built a career bridging government service and internat
 ional corporate strategy\, managing global teams and connecting policy\, 
 advocacy\, and market access for one of the world's leading pharmaceutica
 l companies. She'll share real-world strategies that helped her move from
  Capitol Hill to global leadership—and how you can apply them too.</p><
 p data-start="844" data-end="886"><strong data-start="844" data-end="884"
 >What you'll get out of this session:</strong></p><ul data-start="887" da
 ta-end="1235"><li data-start="887" data-end="975"><p data-start="889" dat
 a-end="975">      How to approach professionals\, start conversations\, a
 nd make connections that matter    </p></li><li data-start="976" data-end
 ="1073"><p data-start="978" data-end="1073">      Insider strategies for 
 turning networking into internships\, mentors\, and career opportunities 
    </p></li><li data-start="1074" data-end="1154"><p data-start="1076" da
 ta-end="1154">      Tools to tell your story confidently in interviews an
 d professional settings    </p></li><li data-start="1155" data-end="1235"
 ><p data-start="1157" data-end="1235">      Tips for navigating global co
