BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"IU Hamilton Lugar School": "https://events.iu.edu/live/events/2009760-ostrom-workshop-research-series-adriana-abreu"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_hamilton_lugar
X-SOURCE:IU Hamilton Lugar School
DTSTART:20260408T160000Z
DTEND:20260408T170000Z
LOCATION:The Ostrom Workshop\, 513 N PARK AVE - Room Number: Tocqueville
GEO:39.171057;-86.524959
SUMMARY:CANCELED: Ostrom Workshop | Research Series: Adriana Abreu
DESCRIPTION:Bio  Adriana is an Amazonian environmental anthropologist foc
 using on resource management\, traditional communities\, conservation\, g
 ender equity\, development\, and socioenvironmental challenges in the Bra
 zilian Amazon. She holds a B.A. in Social Sciences and an M.A. in Sociolo
 gy &amp\; Anthropology from the University of Pará\, Brazil. Over the pa
 st decade\, she has been involved in researching socioenvironmental confl
 icts\, development\, and the resistance of rural communities in Amazonia 
 as an activist-scholar. Adriana was previously a grantee of the Amazon Ra
 inforest Fund\, contributing to the journalist collaborative project "Qui
 lombolas\, Invisible Protectors of the Forest\, in Sight of COVID-19" htt
 ps://pulitzercenter.org/projects/quilombolas-invisble-protectors-forest-s
 ight-covid-19-portuguese (https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/
 ?url=https%3A%2F%2Fpulitzercenter.org%2Fprojects%2Fquilombolas-invisble-p
 rotectors-forest-sight-covid-19-portuguese&amp\;data=05%7C02%7Cmackka%40i
 u.edu%7Ccd4eb2a425784381849508ddd389bf51%7C1113be34aed14d00ab4bcdd02510be
 91%7C1%7C0%7C638899310768561227%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiO
 nRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%
 3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp\;sdata=OEEE0nioleIGY2XjOsqO%2BNCZcPMfqzT%2B%2FXhDn5n5
 2Bs%3D&amp\;reserved=0). Currently pursuing her Ph.D. in Anthropology at 
 Indiana University\, Adriana's research focuses on the intersection of fo
 rmal rules and social norms in the arapaima fisheries community-based man
 agement. She is part of the project "Integrating Cross-scale Socio-Ecolog
 ical Feedbacks in Freshwater Fisheries" co-led by Professor Eduardo Brond
 izio and is a member of the Center for Analysis of Socio-Ecological Lands
 capes (CASEL) at Indiana University.About the Ostrom Workshop Research Se
 ries  Learn about innovative research by Graduate Students and Visiting S
 cholars as they advance the mission of the Ostrom Workshop\, building upo
 n the theme of governance to understand and address major societal proble
 ms.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><picture class="lw_image lw_image27417 lw
 _align_left lw_block"><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://events.iu
 .edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/105/width/300/height/247/27417_2025_Adriana_
 Abreucrop_2.webp 2x\, https://events.iu.edu/live/image/scale/3x/gid/105/w
 idth/300/height/247/27417_2025_Adriana_Abreucrop_2.webp 3x" data-origin="
 responsive"/><source type="image/png" srcset="https://events.iu.edu/live/
 image/scale/2x/gid/105/width/300/height/247/27417_2025_Adriana_Abreucrop_
 2.rev.1754509838.png 2x\, https://events.iu.edu/live/image/scale/3x/gid/1
 05/width/300/height/247/27417_2025_Adriana_Abreucrop_2.rev.1754509838.png
  3x" data-origin="responsive"/><img width="300" height="247" alt="" data-
 alt="" data-decoration="true" src="https://events.iu.edu/live/image/gid/1
 05/width/300/height/247/27417_2025_Adriana_Abreucrop_2.rev.1754509838.png
 " title="2025 Adriana Abreucrop" srcset="https://events.iu.edu/live/image
 /scale/2x/gid/105/width/300/height/247/27417_2025_Adriana_Abreucrop_2.rev
 .1754509838.png 2x\, https://events.iu.edu/live/image/scale/3x/gid/105/wi
 dth/300/height/247/27417_2025_Adriana_Abreucrop_2.rev.1754509838.png 3x" 
 data-max-w="1498" data-max-h="1232" loading="lazy" data-optimized="true"/
 ></picture></p><p><strong>Bio</strong></p><p>  Adriana is an Amazonian en
 vironmental anthropologist focusing on resource management\, traditional 
 communities\, conservation\, gender equity\, development\, and socioenvir
 onmental challenges in the Brazilian Amazon. She holds a B.A. in Social S
 ciences and an M.A. in Sociology &amp\; Anthropology from the University 
 of Pará\, Brazil. Over the past decade\, she has been involved in resear
 ching socioenvironmental conflicts\, development\, and the resistance of 
 rural communities in Amazonia as an activist-scholar. Adriana was previou
 sly a grantee of the Amazon Rainforest Fund\, contributing to the journal
 ist collaborative project "Quilombolas\, Invisible Protectors of the Fore
 st\, in Sight of COVID-19" <a href="https://nam12.safelinks.protection.ou
 tlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fpulitzercenter.org%2Fprojects%2Fquilombolas-
 invisble-protectors-forest-sight-covid-19-portuguese&amp\;data=05%7C02%7C
 mackka%40iu.edu%7Ccd4eb2a425784381849508ddd389bf51%7C1113be34aed14d00ab4b
 cdd02510be91%7C1%7C0%7C638899310768561227%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB
 0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldU
 IjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp\;sdata=OEEE0nioleIGY2XjOsqO%2BNCZcPMfqzT%2B
 %2FXhDn5n52Bs%3D&amp\;reserved=0">https://pulitzercenter.org/projects/qui
 lombolas-invisble-protectors-forest-sight-covid-19-portuguese</a>. Curren
 tly pursuing her Ph.D. in Anthropology at Indiana University\, Adriana's 
 research focuses on the intersection of formal rules and social norms in 
 the arapaima fisheries community-based management. She is part of the pro
 ject "Integrating Cross-scale Socio-Ecological Feedbacks in Freshwater Fi
 sheries" co-led by Professor Eduardo Brondizio and is a member of the Cen
 ter for Analysis of Socio-Ecological Landscapes (CASEL) at Indiana Univer
 sity.</p><p><strong>About the Ostrom Workshop Research Series</strong></p
 ><p>  Learn about innovative research by Graduate Students and Visiting S
 cholars as they advance the mission of the Ostrom Workshop\, building upo
 n the theme of governance to understand and address major societal proble
 ms.</p>
