SUMMARY:Homeschool Day: Map Making PM Session
DESCRIPTION:Students will explore paintings of landscapes and landmarks i
 n the galleries\, then imagine themselves as travelers journeying to new 
 lands. Back in the studio\, we'll ask questions about territories\, terra
 ins\, and landmarks\, as we design and create our own imaginative maps.Kn
 ow Before You Go:  Meet us on the 1st floor of the museum at 1 p.m. Toget
 her\, we'll drop off personal items in the Simpson Center for Education b
 efore exploring the galleries. After seeing artworks that will inspire ou
 r project\, we'll head back to the Roehm Family Art-Making Studio to crea
 te our own masterpieces! Don't forget to dress for a mess!  Strollers are
  welcome. Chaperones required. We ask that chaperones be 18 or older\, wi
 th one adult for every 6 children.Parking Information:  The museum is in 
 the pedestrian district of campus with several parking options nearby. Th
 e Indiana Memorial Union lot (900 E. 7th Street) is just a 5-minute walk 
 diagonal to the museum\, and visitors can receive 40% off parking validat
 ion at the museum's guest services desk. The East Garage (105 N. Eagleson
  Ave.) and Fee Lane Garage (709 N. Fee Lane) are also convenient\, about 
 an 8–10 minute walk. Learn more about parking on the Bloomington campus
  here (https://parking.indiana.edu/facilities/index.html).
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Students will explore paintings of land
 scapes and landmarks in the galleries\, then imagine themselves as travel
 ers journeying to new lands. Back in the studio\, we'll ask questions abo
 ut territories\, terrains\, and landmarks\, as we design and create our o
 wn imaginative maps.</p><p><strong>Know Before You Go:</strong></p><p>  M
 eet us on the 1st floor of the museum at 1 p.m. Together\, we'll drop off
  personal items in the Simpson Center for Education before exploring the 
 galleries. After seeing artworks that will inspire our project\, we'll he
 ad back to the Roehm Family Art-Making Studio to create our own masterpie
 ces! Don't forget to dress for a mess!</p><p>  Strollers are welcome. Cha
 perones required. We ask that chaperones be 18 or older\, with one adult 
 for every 6 children.</p><p><strong>Parking Information:</strong></p><p> 
  The museum is in the pedestrian district of campus with several parking 
 options nearby. The Indiana Memorial Union lot (900 E. 7th Street) is jus
 t a 5-minute walk diagonal to the museum\, and visitors can receive 40% o
 ff parking validation at the museum's guest services desk. The East Garag
 e (105 N. Eagleson Ave.) and Fee Lane Garage (709 N. Fee Lane) are also c
 onvenient\, about an 8–10 minute walk. Learn more about parking on the 
 Bloomington campus <a class="external" href="https://parking.indiana.edu/
 facilities/index.html">here</a>.</p>
