CATEGORIES:Fundraiser/Philanthropy
CATEGORIES:Health & Wellness
DESCRIPTION:The Theta Chapter of Sigma Lambda Beta International Fraternit
 y Inc. is planning a reproductive rights expo\, a small-scale\, interacti
 ve event designed to educate and engage the university community on criti
 cal issues affecting women’s rights\, gender equity\, and reproductive ch
 oice. The event will feature themed tables staffed by volunteers or organ
 izational representatives\, where attendees can explore topics\, ask ques
 tions\, and participate in hands-on activities. Think of it as a college-
 style fair focused on women’s issues\, with each table serving as a mini-
 workshop or information hub. It will not be a protest nor a political dem
 onstration\, rather it will be an informational event. There will also be
  a philanthropic element\, as one of the tables will be constructing care
  packages (containing pads\, soap\, toothbrush/toothpaste\, socks\, glove
 s\, protein bars\, water\, nuts\, trail mix\, etc.) which will be donated
  to Middle Way House.\n\nHosted by: Sigma Lambda Beta Fraternity\, Inc.\n
 \nAdditional Information can be found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/
 event/12302159
DTEND:20260409T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260409T210000Z
LOCATION:IMU Dogwood Room
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Reproductive Rights Expo
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12302159
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12302159
X-HOSTS:Sigma Lambda Beta Fraternity\, Inc.
END:VEVENT
