DESCRIPTION:This hands-on workshop has a registration fee\, and pre-registr
 ation is required.<br>Register online by April 8 at <a href="https://webtra
 c.bloomington.in.gov/webtrac/web/search.html?Primarycode=140010">https://we
 btrac.bloomington.in.gov/webtrac/web/search.html?Primarycode=140010</a><br>
 $15/in-city\, $17/non-city. For all ages.<br><br>Help support our winged fr
 iends as the great northern bird migration peaks the first of May. In this 
 program\, we will talk about some of the more unique bird species that will
  be moving through the area\, before constructing bird feeders to support t
 hem in their travels north. All materials are provided. Come with a constru
 ctive\, hands-on attitude\, and leave with a one-of-a-kind bird feeder. Cos
 t is per project\, and up to two people can work on a project together. Onl
 y one person needs to register per pair. Be sure to register for the number
  of feeders you would like to create.
LAST-MODIFIED:20251118T191405Z
LOCATION:Allison Jukebox Community Center\, 351 S Washington St\, Bloomingt
 on\, IN 47401\, USA
