X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Brown County Playhouse": "https://browncountyplayhouse.org/event/1984-radio-play/2026-04-11/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:brown_county_playhouse
X-SOURCE:Brown County Playhouse
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260411T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260411T220000
DTSTAMP:20260308T215238
CREATED:20260226T163148Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260303T184901Z
UID:10001418-1775935800-1775944800@browncountyplayhouse.org
SUMMARY:1984 - Radio Play
DESCRIPTION:In a world where every thought is monitored and the Party controls truth itself\, Winston Smith dares to question the system. When forbidden love awakens him to the possibility of freedom\, he risks everything in a chilling battle against a regime where even thinking differently is a crime.\n\n\n \n\n\nDisclaimer: This production explores themes of government control\, surveillance\, and personal freedom within a fictional world. While it addresses sensitive political subject matter\, it is not intended as commentary on current events\, political parties\, or today’s social climate. Its purpose is to tell a compelling story and encourage thoughtful reflection\, not to promote a particular political viewpoint.\n\nTickets - Friday\, April 10\, 7:30pm\n\nTickets - Saturday\, April 11\, 7:30pm\n\nTickets - Sunday\, April 12\, 2:30pm\n\n  \nCast:\nNarrator\, Guard – Tom Preston\nTelescreen – Horace Tucker\nBig Brother – Chad Carrotkers\nWinston Smith – Daniel Ott\nO’Brien – Sheila Popplewell\nJulia – Jessica Pumo\nInner Voice – Tony Sanchez\nSyme – Jerry Maguire\nTom Parsons – Brenden King\nAmpleforth – Harold Crooks\nCharrington – Kristy Kelley\nMillie Parsons – Marlee Wigner\nProle Voice – Dawn Fleming\nBumstead (Prisoner) – Kaylin Creeden\nGuard – Robert Stevens\nVoice – Amber Compton\nVoice – Larry Compton\nVoice – Franklin Connor\nVoice – Maria Rust\nVoice – Greg Scherschel\nVoice – Tim Sparks \nCrew:\nDirector\, Sound Design – Joshua Lane\nAssistant Director\, Lighting Designer – Dania Leova\nProduction Manager – Brian Heaton\nCostume Manager – Sidney Bolam\nStage Manager – Wendi Gore\nFoley Artist – Tony Brewer\nMusic Maestro – Chuck Wills\nLighting Director – Allie Mattox\nProduction Assistant – Roger Ata \nTickets - Friday\, April 10\, 7:30pm\n\nTickets - Saturday\, April 11\, 7:30pm\n\nTickets - Sunday\, April 12\, 2:30pm\n\n 
URL:https://browncountyplayhouse.org/event/1984-radio-play/2026-04-11/
LOCATION:Brown County Playhouse\, 70 S. Van Buren St\, Nashville\, IN\, 47448\, United States
CATEGORIES:Featured Event,Live Shows,Radio Play
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://browncountyplayhouse.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2026-1984_web_event.jpg
END:VEVENT
