X-SOURCE-URLS:{"IU Maurer School of Law": "https://events.iu.edu/lawiub/event/2129695-let-them-make-contracts-rehabilitating-lochner"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_maurer_law
X-SOURCE:IU Maurer School of Law
DTSTART:20260413T160000Z
DTEND:20260413T170000Z
LOCATION:LOWELL E. BAIER HALL/IU MAURER SCHOOL OF LAW - Room Number: 125
GEO:39.165074;-86.526424
SUMMARY:Let Them Make Contracts: Rehabilitating Lochner
DESCRIPTION:Professor David Bernstein of George Mason University's Antoni
 n Scalia Law School\, joined by Professor Steve Sanders\, will discuss th
 e rise\, fall\, and influence of Lochner. How far should the liberty of c
 ontract extend against the police power of the State? What is the role of
  courts in protecting that liberty? How did Lochner influence judicial re
 cognition of individual rights in the 20th century? Was Lochner truly an 
 aberration from liberty of contract doctrine? Join us for a conversation 
 on the history\, merits\, pitfalls\, and impact of Lochner in the America
 n constitutional scheme.  Noodles &amp\; Company will be provided for all
  attendees!&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Professor David Bernstein of George Mas
 on University's Antonin Scalia Law School\, joined by Professor Steve San
 ders\, will discuss the rise\, fall\, and influence of Lochner. How far s
 hould the liberty of contract extend against the police power of the Stat
 e? What is the role of courts in protecting that liberty? How did Lochner
  influence judicial recognition of individual rights in the 20th century?
  Was Lochner truly an aberration from liberty of contract doctrine? Join 
 us for a conversation on the history\, merits\, pitfalls\, and impact of 
 Lochner in the American constitutional scheme.</p><p>  Noodles &amp\; Com
 pany will be provided for all attendees!&#160\;</p>
UID:20260413T160000Z-2129695@events.iu.edu
DTSTAMP:20251125T142122Z
