SUMMARY:ACC Book Club features "To Save and Destroy" by Viet Nguyen
DESCRIPTION:What does it mean to be&#160\;an "other"? How can writing shi
 ft the boundaries between insider and outsider for both author and audien
 ce? All are welcome to join the ACC in discussing these questions over di
 nner through Viet Thanh Nguyen's essay collection&#160\;To Save and&#160\
 ;to Destroy: Writing as an Other. Originally delivered as the Norton Lect
 ure series at Harvard in 2023-24\, the six chapters span Nguyen's reflect
 ions on war\, solidarity\, and power\, drawing from sources ranging from 
 classics of American literature to Nguyen's own lived experience as a ref
 ugee. Digital copies of the eBook are&#160\;freely available to access th
 rough IU Libraries\, so all attendees are welcome to read ahead! Pizza wi
 ll be served at each meeting.&#160\;For more information\, please reach o
 ut to ACC volunteer and book club moderator Cheryl Nong\, PhD student in 
 social psychology\, at&#160\;acc@iu.edu. The next book club meeting is on
  March 26\, 2026.&#160\;&#160\;All Indiana University events\, groups\, a
 ctivities\, and&#160\;educational\, cultural\, and historical observances
  welcome all IU students and other members of the Indiana University comm
 unity.For more information\, view this event in BeInvolved (https://beinv
 olved.indiana.edu/event/11950465).
