  our successes\, and identifying the students who will receive their MAP 
 Certificate of Completion!\nThe Mentor Apprenticeship Program (MAP) is a 
 two-semester training series facilitated by the FASE Mentoring Program. I
 t gives students at IU Bloomington opportunities to enhance their mentori
 ng\, teamwork\, and leadership skills. Upon completion of MAP\, students 
 receive a Certificate of Completion\, which establishes their commitment 
 to growth and leadership.\nAll Indiana University events\, groups\, activ
 ities\, and educational\, cultural\, and historical observances welcome a
 ll IU students and other members of the Indiana University community.\n\n
 Hosted by: Mentoring Services and Leadership Development \n\nAdditional I
 nformation can be found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11350130
