CATEGORIES:ThoughtfulLearning
CATEGORIES:Engage & Thrive - Wellbeing
DESCRIPTION:Curious about taking a break from cannabis or wanting to bette
 r understand your relationship with it? Join us for an interactive T-Brea
 k Workshop based on the T-Break Guide by Tom Fontana. This session explor
 es what a 21-day cannabis tolerance break can look like and offers practi
 cal tools for navigating common experiences like cravings\, sleep changes
 \, mood shifts\, and stress.\nParticipants will learn about the physical\
 , emotional\, and reflective themes that often come up during a T-Break\,
  engage in guided discussion\, and explore strategies for creating balanc
 e — whether your goal is to reset your tolerance\, take a short pause\, o
 r simply reflect on your use. This workshop is supportive\, educational\,
  and judgment-free. No prior experience with a T-Break is required.\n\nHo
 sted by: Collegiate Recovery Community\n\nAdditional Information can be f
 ound at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12166185
DTEND:20260421T223000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020709Z
DTSTART:20260421T213000Z
LOCATION:The Wellness House
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:T-Break Workshop
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12166185
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12166185
X-HOSTS:Collegiate Recovery Community
END:VEVENT
