BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"IU Hamilton Lugar School": "https://events.iu.edu/live/events/2199397-spring-2026-colloquium-series-with-lucia-guerra", "IU La Casa Latino Cultural Center": "https://events.iu.edu/live/events/2199397-spring-2026-colloquium-series-with-lucia-guerra"}
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"IU Hamilton Lugar School": "https://events.iu.edu/live/events/2199397-spring-2026-colloquium-series-with-lucia-guerra"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_hamilton_lugar
X-SOURCE:IU Hamilton Lugar School, IU La Casa Latino Cultural Center
DTSTART:20260427T200000Z
DTEND:20260427T210000Z
LOCATION:355 N. Eagleson Avenue - Room Number: 1060
SUMMARY:Spring 2026 Colloquium Series with Lucia Guerra Reyes
DESCRIPTION:The Center for Latin American and Caribbean Studies is proud 
 to present the continuation of its Colloquium Series for Spring 2026.  We
  welcome Dr. Lucia Guerra Reyes&#160\;as she presents Circulating Latin A
 merica: Ethical Interventions from the Global South.Lucia Guerra-Reyes is
  an associate professor in applied health science. She is a medical anthr
 opologist and interdisciplinary researcher. Guerra-Reyes investigates the
  complexities of access to sexual and reproductive health and care for ma
 rginalized communities. She is interested in understanding how national p
 olicies of culturally appropriate care are enacted at the local level\; h
 ow health care providers view their role in extending care to under-serve
 d communities\; and how women make decisions about their reproductive liv
 es.&#160\;  &#160\;  The CLACS Spring 2026 Colloquium meets Mondays from 
 February through April\, with faculty and guest speakers engaging Latin A
 merica and the Caribbean through research on history\, culture\, language
 \, politics\, and the arts. Check the CLACS Calendar (https://events.iu.e
 du/clacs/) for details.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The Center for Latin American and Carib
 bean Studies is proud to present the continuation of its <strong>Colloqui
 um Series for Spring 2026</strong>.</p><p>  We welcome <strong>Dr. Lucia 
 Guerra Reyes</strong>&#160\;as she presents <em><strong>Circulating Latin
  America: Ethical Interventions from the Global South.</strong></em></p><
 p><strong>Lucia Guerra-Reyes</strong> is an associate professor in applie
 d health science. She is a medical anthropologist and interdisciplinary r
 esearcher. <strong>Guerra-Reyes</strong> investigates the complexities of
  access to sexual and reproductive health and care for marginalized commu
 nities. She is interested in understanding how national policies of cultu
 rally appropriate care are enacted at the local level\; how health care p
 roviders view their role in extending care to under-served communities\; 
 and how women make decisions about their reproductive lives.&#160\;</p><p
 >  &#160\;</p><p>  The CLACS Spring 2026 Colloquium meets Mondays from Fe
