SUMMARY:Global Competencies Skills Development Series: Off-the-Record Din
 ner on Careers in Intelligence & National Security
DESCRIPTION:What does it actually take to build a career in intelligence 
 or the White House?  Join a small\, off-the-record dinner with Judd Dever
 mont\, former National Intelligence Officer and senior National Security 
 Council official who helped shape U.S. policy at the highest levels of go
 vernment.  This is not a speech. It is a direct conversation.  He has wor
 ked inside the intelligence community\, coordinated across agencies\, and
  advised senior decision-makers on complex global crises. He has seen how
  power moves\, how policy is negotiated\, and how careers are built or st
 alled.  We will talk about:      Breaking into intelligence and national 
 security          Moving between government\, analysis\, and policy roles
           Negotiation and coalition building in real-world settings      
     The risks\, trade-offs\, and personal decisions behind public service
           What early-career professionals get wrong      If you are serio
 us about a future in intelligence\, national security\, or global affairs
 \, this is a rare chance to ask unfiltered questions in a closed-door set
 ting.  Space is limited.
