EXDATE;TZID=America/New_York:20260509T083000
DTSTAMP:20260309T020653Z
UID:0hjhbp33a7qqsnnqgqu95dbq1g@google.com
CREATED:20251205T170614Z
DESCRIPTION:Participation is free but registration is required\; register b
 y April 27 online at <a href="https://webtrac.bloomington.in.gov/webtrac/we
 b/search.html?Primarycode=140012">https://webtrac.bloomington.in.gov/webtra
 c/web/search.html?Primarycode=140012</a><br>For ages 15 yrs. and up.<br>Lea
 rn how to restore pollinator habitat with the Bloomington Parks and Recreat
 ion Urban Greenspace team and biologists from the US Fish and Wildlife Serv
 ice (USFWS) Partners for Fish and Wildlife (PFW) Program. Topics to be cove
 red include site selection and design\, site preparation\, plant selection\
 , planting methods and maintenance\, pollinator ID\, and plant ID. The goal
  of this workshop series is to provide participants with the tools and know
 ledge to transform small areas of unused land (e.g. home\, school\, and chu
 rch yards) into native pollinator habitat. Participants must commit to both
  workshop dates.
LAST-MODIFIED:20251205T170634Z
LOCATION:Switchyard Park\, 1601 S Rogers St\, Bloomington\, IN 47403\, USA
