BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Eskenazi Museum of Art": "https://events.iu.edu/artmuseum/event/2093916-family-art-lab"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_eskenazi_museum
X-SOURCE:Eskenazi Museum of Art
DTSTART:20260503T170000Z
DTEND:20260503T190000Z
LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART - Room Number: Roehm Fami
 ly Art-making Studio
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Family Art Lab
DESCRIPTION:Please note&#160\;that&#160\;this month's Family Art Lab does
  not follow&#160\;the second Sunday schedule.  Designed for K-12 students
  and their families\, this event offers a fun and flexible way to spark c
 reativity and connect with each other. All ages and experience levels are
  welcome!  Come and go at your own pace. We recommend planning for at lea
 st an hour to explore the gallery and make art.  Start in the Art Studio 
 inside the Kimberly and John Simpson Center for Education on the museum's
  2nd floor to pick up your Gallery Challenge. Then head to the galleries 
 to find the artwork we'll use as inspiration for our project! When you're
  ready\, head back to the studio for our hands-on art-making activity tha
 t everyone will love.  This program takes place every Second Sunday of th
 e month\, excluding holidays and museum closures. Each month features new
  artworks and materials\, so there's always something fresh to explore an
 d create!  All children must be chaperoned.Know Before You Go:Read about 
 where to find us\, where to park\, accessibility\, and museum guidelines.
 Strollers are welcome in the galleries. When carrying small children\, pl
 ease keep them in front of you.  To save time at the lockers\, avoid brin
 ging backpacks or large bags.  When You Arrive:If you parked in the IMU p
 arking lot\, Guest Services can validate your parking voucher for a disco
 unt.  Store any large bags in the lockers behind the Guest Services desk.
   Head upstairs to the 2nd Floor and into the Simpson Center for Educatio
 n to start.  When in the galleries\, do not touch the artwork. Be mindful
  to keep body parts and anything you're carrying at least 18" away from t
 he art.  Photography is welcome! Just no flash or selfie sticks.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><strong>Please note</strong><span style="
 box-sizing: border-box\; margin: 0px\; padding: 0px\;"><strong>&#160\;</s
 trong>that<strong>&#160\;</strong>this month's Family Art Lab does not fo
 llow</span>&#160\;the second Sunday schedule.</p><p>  Designed for K-12 s
 tudents and their families\, this event offers a fun and flexible way to 
 spark creativity and connect with each other. All ages and experience lev
 els are welcome!</p><p>  Come and go at your own pace. We recommend plann
 ing for at least an hour to explore the gallery and make art.</p><p>  Sta
 rt in the Art Studio inside the Kimberly and John Simpson Center for Educ
 ation on the museum's 2nd floor to pick up your Gallery Challenge. Then h
 ead to the galleries to find the artwork we'll use as inspiration for our
  project! When you're ready\, head back to the studio for our hands-on ar
 t-making activity that everyone will love.</p><p>  This program takes pla
 ce every Second Sunday of the month\, excluding holidays and museum closu
 res. Each month features new artworks and materials\, so there's always s
 omething fresh to explore and create!</p><p>  All children must be chaper
 oned.</p><p><strong>Know Before You Go:</strong></p><ul><li>Read about <a
  class="external" href="https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/visit/your-visit.ht
 ml"><span data-contrast="none">where to find us\, where to park\, accessi
 bility\, and museum guidelines</span></a><span data-contrast="auto">.</sp
 an></li><li>Strollers are welcome in the galleries. When carrying small c
 hildren\, please keep them in front of you.  </li><li>To save time at the
  lockers\, avoid bringing backpacks or large bags.  </li></ul><p><strong>
 When You Arrive:</strong></p><ul><li>If you parked in the IMU parking lot
 \, Guest Services can validate your parking voucher for a discount.  </li
 ><li>Store any large bags in the lockers behind the Guest Services desk. 
  </li><li>Head upstairs to the 2nd Floor and into the Simpson Center for 
 Education to start.  </li><li>When in the galleries\, do not touch the ar
 twork. Be mindful to keep body parts and anything you're carrying at leas
 t 18" away from the art.  </li><li>Photography is welcome! Just no flash 
 or selfie sticks.  </li></ul>
