CATEGORIES:Campus-Wide Event
DESCRIPTION:Our Wilderness First Aid (WFA) courses will give you the skill
 s needed to respond to medical emergencies when help is far away.\nThis i
 s a 2-day/16-hour course that features extensive hands-on learning opport
 unities. Students will walk away with a 2-year WFA certification from Sto
 nehearth Open Learning Opportunities (SOLO)\, which is one of the oldest 
 wilderness medicine organizations in the world.\nStudents may also add on
  CPR modules and/or re-certify for their SOLO Wilderness First Responder 
 (WFR) certification.\nCourses start at $275. Cost includes course materia
 ls and lunch on Saturday and Sunday. Overnight lodging from Friday–Sunday
  may be available for participants on a first-come\, first-serve basis.\n
 Register for the course here.\n\nHosted by: Bradford Woods\n\nAdditional 
 Information can be found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/1212272
 6
