LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART - Room Number: Simpson Ce
 nter for Education
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Homeschool Day: America 250 PM Session
DESCRIPTION:Travel back in time with us to America in 1776 to meet George
  Washington and see the Declaration of Independence up close. Together\, 
 we'll explore the art and stories that shaped our nation's founding. Afte
 rwards\, we'll create our own colonial-inspired artwork in the studio\, r
 eflecting on the theme of "What America Means to Me."Know Before You Go: 
  Meet us on the 1st floor of the museum at 1 p.m. Together\, we'll drop o
 ff personal items in the Simpson Center for Education before exploring th
 e galleries. After seeing artworks that will inspire our project\, we'll 
 head back to the Roehm Family Art-Making Studio to create our own masterp
 ieces! Don't forget to dress for a mess!  Strollers are welcome. Chaperon
 es required. We ask that chaperones be 18 or older\, with one adult for e
 very 6 children.Parking Information:  The museum is in the pedestrian dis
 trict of campus with several parking options nearby. The Indiana Memorial
  Union lot (900 E. 7th Street) is just a 5-minute walk diagonal to the mu
 seum\, and visitors can receive 40% off parking validation at the museum'
 s guest services desk. The East Garage (105 N. Eagleson Ave.) and Fee Lan
 e Garage (709 N. Fee Lane) are also convenient\, about an 8–10 minute w
 alk. Learn more about parking on the Bloomington campus here (https://par
 king.indiana.edu/facilities/index.html).
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Travel back in time with us to America 
 in 1776 to meet George Washington and see the Declaration of Independence
  up close. Together\, we'll explore the art and stories that shaped our n
 ation's founding. Afterwards\, we'll create our own colonial-inspired art
 work in the studio\, reflecting on the theme of "What America Means to Me
 ."</p><p><strong>Know Before You Go:</strong></p><p>  Meet us on the 1st 
 floor of the museum at 1 p.m. Together\, we'll drop off personal items in
  the Simpson Center for Education before exploring the galleries. After s
 eeing artworks that will inspire our project\, we'll head back to the Roe
 hm Family Art-Making Studio to create our own masterpieces! Don't forget 
 to dress for a mess!</p><p>  Strollers are welcome. Chaperones required. 
 We ask that chaperones be 18 or older\, with one adult for every 6 childr
 en.</p><p><strong>Parking Information:</strong></p><p>  The museum is in 
 the pedestrian district of campus with several parking options nearby. Th
 e Indiana Memorial Union lot (900 E. 7th Street) is just a 5-minute walk 
 diagonal to the museum\, and visitors can receive 40% off parking validat
 ion at the museum's guest services desk. The East Garage (105 N. Eagleson
  Ave.) and Fee Lane Garage (709 N. Fee Lane) are also convenient\, about 
 an 8–10 minute walk. Learn more about parking on the Bloomington campus
  <a href="https://parking.indiana.edu/facilities/index.html">here</a>.</p
