X-SOURCE-URLS:{"IU Bloomington Libraries": "https://events.iu.edu/libraries/event/2213132-declaration-of-independence-curator-talks"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_libraries
X-SOURCE:IU Bloomington Libraries
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260613
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260614
LOCATION:LILLY LIBRARY
GEO:39.167909;-86.518974
SUMMARY:Declaration of Independence Curator Talks
DESCRIPTION:The Declaration of Independence: The Motives\, The Moment is 
 an exhibition exploring the journey taken by the nation's founders. How c
 olonial leaders go from loyal subjects of the British empire to risking e
 verything by becoming revolutionaries? Take an insightful tour of the exh
 ibition from the curator\, with up close looks at Revolutionary War era c
 orrespondence\, books and manuscripts that influenced the revolutionaries
 \, and media that spread the word about the declaration.  Light refreshme
 nts will be offered. Come learn something new about the nation's founding
  and have a snack in Indiana University's rare book library!  Tours are o
 ffered at noon\, 1 p.m.\, and 2 p.m. RSVP requested for planning of refre
 shments and staffing.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><em>The Declaration of Independence: The 
 Motives\, The Moment</em> is an exhibition exploring the journey taken by
  the nation's founders. How colonial leaders go from loyal subjects of th
 e British empire to risking everything by becoming revolutionaries? Take 
 an insightful tour of the exhibition from the curator\, with up close loo
 ks at Revolutionary War era correspondence\, books and manuscripts that i
 nfluenced the revolutionaries\, and media that spread the word about the 
 declaration.</p><p>  Light refreshments will be offered. Come learn somet
 hing new about the nation's founding and have a snack in Indiana Universi
 ty's rare book library!</p><p>  Tours are offered at noon\, 1 p.m.\, and 
 2 p.m. RSVP requested for planning of refreshments and staffing.</p>
UID:20260613T040000Z-2213132@events.iu.edu
DTSTAMP:20260217T111327Z
