BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Hoosier Fly Fishers": "https://www.hoosierflyfishers.com/event/wku-fly-fishing-montana-september-2026/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:hoosierflyfishers_list
X-SOURCE:Hoosier Fly Fishers
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260914
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260920
DTSTAMP:20260308T220725
CREATED:20251230T135841Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251230T140258Z
UID:3757-1789344000-1789862399@www.hoosierflyfishers.com
SUMMARY:WKU Fly Fishing Montana September 2026
DESCRIPTION:AND\nSeptember 20 –  September 25  \nJoin WKU and experience fly fishing on world-renowned\nwaters which contain several trout species and\nother fish such as mountain whitefish\, northern\npikeminnow\, and pike. Guides typically take\nparticipants on one or more of the following\nrivers: Blackfoot\, Clark Fork\, Bitterroot. \nNo prior fly-fishing experience is required.\nThis program is designed to meet the\nneeds of the complete beginner and ‘experts’\nalike; whatever an expert is. All fishing will be\nfrom drift boats or rafts. Being able to cast a\nflyrod is certainly helpful\, but not a requirement\nas on-the-river instruction is readily available.\nWKU has successfully offered this program since\n2012 to participants with a wide range of abilities\n(from no prior experience to being a fly-fishing\nguide). \nhttps://www.wku.edu/flyfishing/
URL:https://www.hoosierflyfishers.com/event/wku-fly-fishing-montana-september-2026/
LOCATION:Mn
CATEGORIES:Events,Fly Fishing Events
ORGANIZER;CN="Dr. Raymond Poff WKU":MAILTO:raymond.poff@wku.edu
END:VEVENT
