CREATED:20260306T125958Z
DESCRIPTION:Please join us on Sunday\, October 4th\, for MCHA's 31st Annual
  Run for the Animals presented by The Dog House!\n\nLearn more & register a
 t monroehumane.org/5k\n\nRun for the Animals is a timed 5K run/walk at Kars
 t Farm Park\, with a portion of the course winding through the Monroe Count
 y Fairgrounds. All of the proceeds benefit the programs and services of Mon
 roe County Humane Association.\n\nNEW in 2026\, we're introducing separate 
 start times for runners and walkers! The course starts at Karst Farm Park a
 nd loops through the Monroe County Fairgrounds. The awards ceremony and spo
 nsor booths are now located near the start/finish line\, making it easier f
 or participants and families to celebrate together—and for faster results p
 osting! After the awards\, stick around for the raffles and fan-favorite pe
 t contests. You don't have to be registered in the 5K to participate in the
  raffle and pet contests!\n\nThis event is so important to MCHA and our abi
 lity to provide programs and services that would otherwise not exist in our
  community\, including accessible veterinary care\, spay/neuter assistance\
 , crisis housing\, emergency pet food & supply pantry\, street outreach\, a
 nd more. MCHA is a private 501c3 non-profit that receives no funding from n
 ational organizations or tax dollars. \n\nWe anticipate welcoming hundreds 
 of runners\, walkers\, and canine friends to this event! Don’t miss this gr
 eat opportunity to support animal welfare in our community!\n\nEVENT SCHEDU
 LE:\n\nSaturday\, October 3\n10:00 AM–12:00 PM & 5:00–7:00 PM: Preregistere
 d Packet Pick-up at Karst Farm Park Commons Bldg\n\nSunday\, October 4\n8:0
 0 AM: Packet Pick-up & Onsite Registration Opens\n9:15 AM: Registration Clo
 ses\, Trainer-led Group Stretch\n9:30 AM: 5K Run Begins\n9:35 AM: 5K Walk B
 egins\n10:30 AM: 5K Run/Walk Awards Ceremony\n11:00 AM: Pet Contests & Raff
 le Winners Announced\n\n\n5K Award Categories:\n\nTop 3 Overall Men's 5K\nT
 op 3 Overall Women's 5K\nTop 3 Youth (12 & under) Male 5K\nTop 3 Youth (12 
 & under) Female 5K\nTop Male & Top Female 13-17 years\nTop Male & Top Femal
 e 18-24 years\nTop Male & Top Female 25-29 years\nTop Male & Top Female 30-
 39 years\nTop Male & Top Female 40-49 years\nTop Male & Top Female 50-59 ye
 ars\nTop Male & Top Female 60+ years\nTop 3 Canine 5K\n\nImportant Notice f
 or Canine Participants: As required by the state of Indiana\, all dogs must
  be up to date on the rabies vaccination. In addition\, only spayed/neutere
 d dogs are permitted to participate. (Visit monroehumane.org for informatio
 n on Spay/Neuter Assistance.) All dogs must remain on a leash at all times 
 during the event. For safety reasons\, retractable leashes are not permitte
 d—only standard\, non-retractable leashes are allowed. Thank you for helpin
 g us ensure a safe and fun event for everyone!\n\n👏👏👏 THANK YOU TO OUR S
 PONSORS:\n\nPRESENTING SPONSOR: The 31st Annual Run for the Animals is pres
 ented by The Dog House\, offering cage-free boarding in a cozy\, home-like 
 environment. With 24-hour staffing and personalized care\, The Dog House st
 rives to be your pet’s home away from home. Learn more at trydoghouse.com.\
 n\nGOLD SPONSORS: Monroe County Parks and Recreation & Monroe County Fairgr
 ounds\nSILVER SPONSORS: BloomingPaws\; German American Bank\; & Slotegraaf 
 Niehoff P.C.\nBRONZE SPONSORS: IU Credit Union & Smithville\n\nhttps://www.
 facebook.com/events/1581183743008999/
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T130000Z
LOCATION:Karst Farm Park
SEQUENCE:5419592
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:31st Annual Run for the Animals 5K
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
